Belgium have been held to a 1-1 draw by Greece in their International friendly encounter played at the Stade Roi Baudouin in Brussel on Thursday. Thorgan Hazard opened the scoring in the 20th minute from a Yannick Carrasco assist. This was equalised in the 66th minute by Georgios Tzavellas. Belgium were without key man Kevin De Bruyne who sustained an injury in the UEFA Champions League final between Manchester City and Chelsea last week. He will also missed his national teamâ€™s first game against Russia at the Euro 2020 on June 12. After the game against Russia, Belgium who are considered favourite to win the tournament will face Denmark and Finland in Group B of the tournament.